avahi4j
Class ResolvedService

java.lang.Object
  avahi4j.ResolvedService

public class ResolvedService
extends java.lang.Object

This class encapsulates the details about a resolved service. It contains:

  • The interface number on the host where the service is offered
  • The IP protocol version the service uses
  • The name of the service
  • The type of the service
  • The domain where the service can be found
  • The name of the host offering the service
  • An Address object containing the IP address of the host
  • The port number where the service is reachable
  • A list of TXT records associated with the service
  • Some lookup result flags (See LOOKUP_RESULT_* in Avahi4JConstants)
  • A ServiceResolver.ServiceResolverEvent object, indicating whether the service could be resolved or not.
Make sure to check the value of resolverEvent first. If it is set to ServiceResolver.ServiceResolverEvent.RESOLVER_FAILURE, other fields are meaningless.

Author:
gilles
